### ğŸ“˜ 2. GitHub Glossary for New Builders

| Term | Meaning | Example |
|------|--------|---------|
| `Repo` | A project folder on GitHub | `visionforge4d/ritualware`  
| `Commit` | A snapshot of changes | â€œAdded authentication logicâ€  
| `Branch` | A separate line of development | `feature/login-ui`  
| `Pull Request (PR)` | A proposed change to merge into main | â€œPlease review and merge this featureâ€  
| `Issue` | A task, bug, or idea | â€œBug: Page not loading on mobileâ€  
| `Fork` | A copy of a repo you can edit freely | Fork a tool to customize for your stack  
| `Clone` | Download the repo locally | `git clone https://github.com/user/repo.git`  
| `Merge` | Combine changes into main code | â€œMerged the PR after reviewâ€  
| `README` | Intro doc in a repo | First thing people see â€” your mission, how to use  
| `Main` | The main branch (used to be `master`) | Where your production-ready code lives  

